text: Meet our pugnacious piebald deer at Sharon Woods  He gets his brown and white mix from a condition known as leucism, which can be found in nearly all mammals. Some have white splotches, some are half brown and half white and some appear nearly all white. Photo: Tim Bugh pic.twitter.com/KEnD3G4x5a
